This paper discusses the use of Generative Adversarial Networks (GANs) for image generation, which falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The paper also analyzes the performance of different GAN frameworks, which is related to machine learning (cs.LG) and graphics (cs.GR). Additionally, the paper discusses the potential applications of GANs in industries such as healthcare and entertainment, which falls under the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category.
